# The build happens INSIDE Docker (multi-stage), so the context is the repo — keep it small and,
# more importantly, keep runtime state out of it.

# These MUST be **/-prefixed. .dockerignore patterns are anchored to the context root, so a bare
# `obj/` matches only a top-level obj — and the one that actually matters is MK.ExcelViewer/obj,
# which on a Windows dev box is full of absolute C:\ paths in project.assets.json. Copy that into
# the Linux build and the restore fails in a thoroughly confusing way.
**/bin/
**/obj/
publish/
.git/
.github/
.vs/
**/*.user
**/*.suo

# Runtime state — must never enter the build context. Do NOT use a bare `data/` pattern here: on a
# case-insensitive filesystem (Windows, macOS) it would also match a `Data/` SOURCE folder.
# (Borrowed from mk-FileConverter's .dockerignore, where that bit someone.)
**/.state/
**/*.db

# Local-only
docker-compose.yml
README.md
shot*.png
